records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, PTC identity theft. Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2.  Motion granted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years, consecutive to the prison sentences imposed on 15 CF 512 and 16 CF 191, to commence upon defendants discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay restitution of $596.45 to Associated Bank. $500.00 cash bail applied;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety;
5) Have no association with any known drug dealers or users;
6) Defendant is to use only one doctor to prescribe medications and only one pharmacist to dispense medications unless approved by the agent;
7) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination of both;
8) Obtain a high school diploma within the first year of release from prison;
9) Provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
10) Pay court costs;
11) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
